{
  "texts": [
    "Through the use of autonomous robotic systems equipped with machine vision, database matching, and various sensors, farmers can benefit from continuous monitoring, intelligent decision-making, and precise agricultural operations, ultimately improving overall crop yield and quality while reducing labor costs and fatigue-related issues (Siddik et al. 2016).",
    "The evolving field of agricultural robotics not only addresses current labor challenges but also drives innovation in developing new techniques (Billingsley et al. 2009; Et Shafiekhani 2017).",
    "Edge computing Edge computing plays a crucial role in enhancing agricultural efficiency by enabling the implementation of advanced technologies in farming practices.",
    "By utilizing edge computing in smart agriculture systems, such as greenhouse farming and precision agriculture, farmers can remotely monitor greenhouses, detect insects, monitor plant health, and optimize crop production (Vimalnath et al. 2023).",
    "Additionally, the integration of artificial intelligence (AI) through machine learning, artificial neural networks, and deep learning further enhances agricultural processes by enabling tasks such as crop disease detection, precision agriculture, and yield estimation (Prajapati et al. 2023)."
  ]
}